---

The sea chart task table (WorldPoint locations, VarbitID completion flags, ObjectID/NpcID
targets and Sailing level requirements for all 358 tasks) is mechanically compiled from the
public game-data constants used by the Sailing plugin by LlemonDuck
(https://github.com/LlemonDuck/sailing), which is also BSD 2-Clause licensed. No code or
creative expression from that project is reused -- only the public Jagex varbit/coordinate
data it had already compiled.

---

Two other small data tables are sourced from the OSRS Wiki (https://oldschool.runescape.wiki),
whose content is published under CC BY-NC-SA 3.0
(https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/): the per-task sea/ocean classification used
to pick a "nearest port" hint (SeaChartRegion.java), sourced from the factual {{SeaChartRow}}
id/sea/ocean fields on the wiki's "Sea charting" page; and the per-sea special-boat-facility
(keel/helm/brazier/inoculation) requirements (SeaChartGearRequirements.java), sourced from the
wiki's per-sea hazard pages. Both extract only factual game-mechanic mappings (which numbered
task/sea needs which facility) rather than the wiki's creative prose, but the OSRS Wiki is
credited here in the interest of good practice.
